# 🎨 Image To Sketch

Convert any image into a realistic pencil sketch using HTML, CSS, and JavaScript.

🔗 Live Demo:  
https://image-to-sketch-1-7byf.onrender.com

---

# 📸 Preview

This project converts uploaded images into:

- ✏️ Pencil Sketch
- 🖼️ White Paper Drawing Effect
- 🎨 Soft Shading Sketch
- 📥 Downloadable Sketch Output

---

# 🚀 Features

✅ Realistic Pencil Sketch Effect  
✅ Upload Any Image  
✅ Download Sketch Output  
✅ Responsive Mobile Design  
✅ Modern Dark UI  
✅ Fixed Screen Layout  
✅ Fast Processing  
✅ No Backend Required  
✅ Fully Client-Side  

---

# 🛠️ Technologies Used

- HTML5
- CSS3
- JavaScript
- Canvas API

---

# 📂 Project Structure

```bash
Image-to-Sketch/
│
├── index.html
├── style.css
├── script.js
├── README.md
└── render.yaml
```

---

# ⚡ How It Works

The application uses:

1. Grayscale Conversion
2. Color Inversion
3. Gaussian Blur
4. Dodge Blend Technique

to generate a realistic pencil sketch effect.

---

# 💻 Run Locally

## Clone Repository

```bash
git clone https://github.com/Sathvik0728/Image-to-Sketch.git
```

## Open Folder

```bash
cd Image-to-Sketch
```

## Run Project

Simply open:

```bash
index.html
```

in your browser.

---

# 🌐 Deployment

This project is deployed on Render as a Static Site.

## Render Deployment

```yaml
services:
  - type: web
    name: image-to-sketch
    env: static
    buildCommand: ""
    staticPublishPath: .
```

